    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Veg Fried Rice</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>2 cups cooked basmati rice, cooled</li>
            <li>1 cup mixed vegetables (carrots, peas, corn, bell peppers), finely chopped</li>
            <li>1/2 cup tofu or paneer, diced (optional)</li>
            <li>3 tablespoons soy sauce</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon sesame oil</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons vegetable oil</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon ginger, minced</li>
            <li>3 cloves garlic, minced</li>
            <li>1/2 cup spring onions, chopped</li>
            <li>1/4 cup cabbage, shredded</li>
            <li>1/4 cup beans, finely chopped</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon black pepper powder</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
            <li>Fresh coriander leaves for garnish</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>vegetarian</li>
            <li>indian</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Heat vegetable oil in a wok or large pan over medium-high heat.</li>
            <li>Add minced ginger and garlic, saut√© for a minute until fragrant.</li>
            <li>Add chopped spring onions and stir-fry for another minute.</li>
            <li>Add diced tofu or paneer (if using) and cook until lightly browned.</li>
            <li>Add mixed vegetables, shredded cabbage, and chopped beans. Stir-fry until the vegetables are tender-crisp.</li>
            <li>Push the vegetables to one side of the wok, add sesame oil to the empty space, and pour the beaten eggs into it. Scramble the eggs until cooked.</li>
            <li>Add cooked and cooled basmati rice to the wok. Mix well with the vegetables and eggs.</li>
            <li>Pour soy sauce over the rice mixture and stir to combine. Ensure even coating of soy sauce.</li>
            <li>Season with black pepper powder and salt to taste. Stir-fry for a few more minutes.</li>
            <li>Garnish with fresh coriander leaves and additional spring onions.</li>
            <li>Serve hot as a delightful Veg Fried Rice.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your flavorful Veg Fried Rice!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>
